==English==

===Etymology===
Noun from Greek [[ψυχή]] (''psychí''/"psee-HEE") 'breath, life, soul, spirit, butterfly'.

===Pronunciation===
*[[International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]]: /ˈsaɪki/ (noun)
*IPA: /ˈsaɪk/ (interjection)

===Noun===
'''psyche'''
# The human [[soul]], [[mind]], or [[spirit]].

===Interjection===
'''psyche'''
# Used abruptly after a sentence to indicate that the speaker is only joking.

